===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|sence}} {{qualifier|archaic}}
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|syns}}, {{m|enm|synnes}}, contraction of earlier {{m|enm|sithens}}, {{m|enm|sithence}}, from {{m|enm|sithen||after, since}} ( + {{m|enm|-s}}, adverbial genitive suffix), from {{inh|en|ang|sīþþan}}, from the phrase {{m|ang||sīþ þǣm|after/since that (time)|sc=Latinx}}, from {{m|ang|sīþ||since, after}} + {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|þǣm}} dative singular of {{m|ang|þæt|}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|sinds||since}}, {{cog|de|seit||since}}, {{cog|da|siden||since}}, {{cog|sco|syne||since}}.
