===Conjunction===
{{en-con}}
# From the time that.
#: {{ux|en|I have loved you '''since''' I first met you.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1913|author={{w|Joseph C. Lincoln}}|section=chapter 6| title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5535161W Mr. Pratt's Patients]| passage=He had one hand on the bounce bottle—and he'd never let go of that '''since''' he got back to the table—but he had a handkerchief in the other and was swabbing his deadlights with it.}}
# [[because|Because]].
#: {{ux|en|'''Since''' you didn't call, we left without you.}}
#* {{RQ:Allingham China Governess|Eye Witness|249|The story struck the depressingly familiar note with which true stories ring in the tried ears of experienced policemen.{{...}}The second note, the high alarum, not so familiar and always important '''since''' it indicates the paramount sin in Man's private calendar, took most of them by surprise although they had been well prepared.}}
#* '''1970''', Jack M. Guttentag, ''New Series on Home Mortgage Yields Since 1951, Volume 92'', {{w|National Bureau of Economic Research}}, [https://books.google.com.au/books?id=BfCpAAAAIAAJ&q=%22since%22&dq=%22since%22&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjI99To5KX0AhWjrlYBHa0cBX8Q6AF6BAgdEAI page 132],
#*: '''Since''' disbursement is the last step in the process of creating a mortgage instrument, the disbursement date may lag the transaction date by a considerable period.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[when|When]] or [[that]].
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 4-2|III|ii|87|2|passage=O ſir ''Iohn'', doe you remember '''ſince''' wee lay all night in the Winde-mill, in S Georges field.}}
